15986\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 11, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104swf1665702804924.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/swf1665702804924.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/swf1665702804924.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"swf1665702804924\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      Transaction Type\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Transaction mode for all operations in the component when run in a distributed transaction processing environment.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"swf1665702804924__topic_d111041e1_d111042e1_d111043e1\">\n         Specify the\n         transaction type property as part of an associated list with the COMMIT (<span class=\"ph uicontrol\">Transaction Auto Commit</span>) property: <p class=\"p\" id=\"swf1665702804924__p_d111044e1_d111045e1_d111046e1\">TYPE=\n               <var class=\"keyword varname\">TypeNumber</var><span class=\"ph gold\">;</span><code class=\"ph codeph\">COMMIT=T</code>|<code class=\"ph codeph\">F</code></p><div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"3\" id=\"swf1665702804924__table_d13013e1_d13014e1_d13015e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"swf1665702804924__table_d13013e1_d13014e1_d13015e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Value</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"swf1665702804924__table_d13013e1_d13014e1_d13015e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Representation</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"swf1665702804924__table_d13013e1_d13014e1_d13015e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">Description</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"swf1665702804924__table_d13013e1_d13014e1_d13015e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">1</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"swf1665702804924__table_d13013e1_d13014e1_d13015e1__entry__2\"> Transaction Support </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"swf1665702804924__table_d13013e1_d13014e1_d13015e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">A global transaction context is not mandatory for the component.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"swf1665702804924__table_d13013e1_d13014e1_d13015e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">2</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"swf1665702804924__table_d13013e1_d13014e1_d13015e1__entry__2\"> No Transaction Support </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"swf1665702804924__table_d13013e1_d13014e1_d13015e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">The component cannot run without a transaction context.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"swf1665702804924__table_d13013e1_d13014e1_d13015e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">3</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"swf1665702804924__table_d13013e1_d13014e1_d13015e1__entry__2\"> Requires Running Transaction </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"swf1665702804924__table_d13013e1_d13014e1_d13015e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">The component can only be used when there is a running transaction. If no\n                           transaction is available, the client starts a new transaction.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"swf1665702804924__table_d13013e1_d13014e1_d13015e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">4</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"swf1665702804924__table_d13013e1_d13014e1_d13015e1__entry__2\"> Requires Transaction </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"swf1665702804924__table_d13013e1_d13014e1_d13015e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">The component requires a transaction. This means that if a transaction is\n                           not present, the component starts and commits its own transaction.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"swf1665702804924__table_d13013e1_d13014e1_d13015e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">5</code>\n</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"swf1665702804924__table_d13013e1_d13014e1_d13015e1__entry__2\"> Requires New Transaction </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"swf1665702804924__table_d13013e1_d13014e1_d13015e1__entry__3\">\n<p class=\"p\">The component requires a new transaction. This means that the component\n                           cannot share the transaction context in which its instance was created.\n                           The component must then start and commit its own transaction.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section table\" id=\"swf1665702804924__section_w2114ab1b5b3_w2115ab1b5_w2116ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1193701e219\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"swf1665702804924__p_d111050e1_d111051e1_d111052e1\">In a distributed transaction environment, the\n            client can start a transaction, and one or more services started by the client can\n            participate in the transaction. When an operation that is located on a server is called,\n            the server changes the DBMS to this transaction, so the service works on a transaction\n            that has already been started.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"swf1665702804924__section_x1f_hn1_dxb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1193701e228\">Applies To</h2>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"swf1665702804924__ul_t4n_3n1_dxb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"swf1665702804924__li_d3113e1_d3114e1_d3115e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ird1665702714456.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ird1665702714456.html\" title=\"A Signature is a Development Object that describes the remote interface of a component, or modeled entity operation. Signatures for Uniface components and modeled entity operations are automatically generated, but signatures for non-Uniface components that Uniface can call at runtime, must be explicitly defined.\">Signature</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jby1665703120046.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Transaction Auto Commit</a><p>Determines whether transactions are committed if the component instance that started the transaction is deleted. Valid values are True or False (default). By default, transactions are rolled back if the component instance is deleted.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mak1665702804857.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Use Transactions</a><p>Determines whether the use of transactions is enabled for the component when run in a distributed transaction processing environment. Valid values are True or False (default).</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615986\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3615986\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Transaction Type Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 11, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Transaction Type Transaction mode for all operations in the component when run in a distributed transaction processing environment. Specify the transaction type property as part of an associated list with the COMMIT ( Transaction Auto Commit ) property: TYPE= TypeNumber ; COMMIT=T | F Value Representation Description 1 Transaction Support A global transaction context is not mandatory for the component. 2 No Transaction Support The component cannot run without a transaction context. 3 Requires Running Transaction The component can only be used when there is a running transaction. If no transaction is available, the client starts a new transaction. 4 Requires Transaction The component requires a transaction. This means that if a transaction is not present, the component starts and commits its own transaction. 5 Requires New Transaction The component requires a new transaction. This means that the component cannot share the transaction context in which its instance was created. The component must then start and commit its own transaction. Description In a distributed transaction environment, the client can start a transaction, and one or more services started by the client can participate in the transaction. When an operation that is located on a server is called, the server changes the DBMS to this transaction, so the service works on a transaction that has already been started. Applies To Signature Related Links Transaction Auto Commit Determines whether transactions are committed if the component instance that started the transaction is deleted. Valid values are True or False (default). By default, transactions are rolled back if the component instance is deleted. Use Transactions Determines whether the use of transactions is enabled for the component when run in a distributed transaction processing environment. Valid values are True or False (default). Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}